[00:17.96]Soft lights melt across the room tonight
[00:20.82]Your shadow dances in the TV light
[00:23.69]You laugh slow like a midnight wave
[00:27.05]And somehow I still drift away
[00:36.07]
[00:42.93]You lean your head against my shoulder
[00:46.21]While the ceiling spins in purple haze
[00:52.58]I should feel complete beside you
[00:55.50]But my mind still wanders through the rain
[01:02.78]
[01:15.05]There’s a comfort in your silence
[01:17.98]Like warm smoke through an open door
[01:24.46]But the quiet of an empty bedroom
[01:27.71]Still pulls me to the floor
[01:33.74]
[01:33.94]I don’t know why
[01:36.46]My heart divides
[01:39.58]Between your touch
[01:42.26]And lonely nights
[01:47.58]
[01:49.06]I love the way your heartbeat sounds
[01:55.34]But I still crave the static now
[02:01.46]Somewhere between the noise and peace
[02:07.86]I lose myself so beautifully
[02:13.64]
[02:14.02]You make the darkness feel alive
[02:20.03]But solitude still feels like home sometimes
[02:26.84]I’m comfortable in your arms
[02:31.78]And even more when I disappear inside myself
[02:39.10]
[03:00.57]We drive through sleeping city avenues
[03:03.68]Neon bleeding on the dashboard glow
[03:10.09]You reach for me like you always do
[03:13.25]But part of me stays in the undertow
[03:19.29]
[03:19.48]Not unhappy
[03:22.26]Not incomplete
[03:25.24]Just tangled in these different kinds of peace
[03:32.10]
[03:32.65]Maybe I was built from empty spaces
[03:38.63]Maybe silence raised me gently
[03:45.49]Maybe love was never meant to cure
[03:50.05]The strange comfort of disappearing
[03:56.19]
[03:56.49]And you understand without asking
[04:08.84]That’s what scares me the most
[04:16.89]
[04:22.53]I love the way your voice cuts through
[04:28.84]The endless spiral in my room
[04:35.04]But when the world goes quiet again
[04:41.37]I still sink into myself like smoke
[04:46.75]
[04:47.09]You make the loneliness feel soft
[04:53.21]Like it was never loneliness at all
[05:00.58]And somewhere in the space between
[05:04.84]Alone and together
[05:07.33]I finally breathe
[05:10.64]
[05:12.46]3AM reflections on the windowpane
[05:18.32]Your sleeping form
[05:20.87]My drifting brain
[05:24.85]And both somehow
[05:31.94]Feel just the same